```

That's a good start! But just to clarify — if you want the function name `read_file` to be platform-agnostic, you could abstract it further inside each #[cfg] block. Alternatively, define an enum or trait with different implementations per OS.

For example:

```rust
trait FileReader {
  fn read(&self) -> Result<String, io::Error>;
}

struct LinuxReader { /* ... */ }
impl FileReader for LinuxReader {}

struct WindowsReader { /* ... */ }
impl FileReader for WindowsReader {}
```
This way, you can switch implementations more flexibly.
